[1] Case update
- Fri 24 Jan 2020. CMRE (Comite Multisectoriel de la Riposte a la maladie a virus Ebola) [in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://mailchi.mp/d94235c459d3/situation-pidmiologique-du-24-janvier-2020?e=b8b1e1fcf3

The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri dated 23 Jan 2020:
- Since the start of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 3416, of which 3297 are confirmed and 119 probable. In total, there were 2240 deaths (2121 confirmed and 119 probable) and 1142 people healed;
- 547 suspected cases under investigation;
- No new confirmed cases;
- 1 new death from confirmed cases, of which no community death was recorded; 1 death from confirmed cases in the Ebola treatment center (ETC) in North Kivu in Mabalako;
- 1 healed person leaving ETC Nord Kivu in Beni;
- No health worker is among the new confirmed cases. The cumulative number of confirmed/probable cases among health workers is 167 (approximately 5% of all confirmed/probable cases), including 41 deaths.

News
The General Coordinator of the response to the Ebola virus disease (EVD) epidemic, Prof. Steve Ahuka Mundeke, chaired this Fri 24 Jan 2020, in the presence of the provincial Minister of Health of North Kivu and partners, the endorsement workshop of the Strategic Plan for the response to the Ebola virus disease epidemic 4.1 (SRP4.1) in the Provinces of North and South Kivu, as well as of Ituri;
- The SRP4.1 endorsement workshop revolved around 2 recommendations from the SRP4 Mid-Term Review, namely, the finalization of inventories of materials and equipment used in the response and that on financial reporting by the Coleads and NGOs. It should be noted that the recommendations of the SRP4 Mid-Term Review were 66.7% completed;
- Discussions from these meetings resulted from the following 5 recommendations: sharing the Ministry of Health's decree on the scale with all stakeholders and the timetable for the development of operational action plans of the sub-coordination units, the institutional analysis of the Provincial Health Divisions (DPS), the harmonization of the budget for SRP4.1 activities planned by the International Federation of the Red Cross (IFRC) and the inclusion in the budget estimate of the rationalization of human resources and the application of the revised premium bonus scale for service providers;
- This workshop, which took place in the meeting room of the Karibu Hotel, headquarters of the General Coordination of the response, in Goma, capital of the province of North Kivu, was attended by members of the General Coordination, the representative of donors, Coleads, international NGOs, Congolese government experts involved in the response.

Vaccination
- A total of 7611 people were vaccinated, as of 22 Jan 2020, with the 2nd vaccine Ad26.ZEBOV/MVA-BN-Filo (Johnson & Johnson) in the 2 health areas from Karisimbi to Goma;
- Since the start of vaccination on 8 Aug 2018 with the rVSV-ZEBOV vaccine, 273 837 people have been vaccinated.

Surveillance at entry points
- Since the start of the epidemic, the total number of travelers checked (temperature taken) at health checkpoints has been 142 573 962.

