[An insightful article raising important points on the situation in the DRC and elsewhere that prevents vaccines from being the end-all solution to pathogen transmission not only in the DRC but also equally in other low- and middle-income countries, especially those where there is social or political unrest. The vaccines, now 2, used in the DRC, as well as the tireless healthcare workers, are thankfully making significant headway in protecting the population from Ebola, but cannot completely prevent disease without other measures being taken to improve security, public health infrastructure, communication to build trust, access to clean water, among others. - Mod.LK

